t: Lord,*sp I cry unto thee: make haste unto me; give ear unto my voice, when I cry unto thee.
Let*p my prayer be set forth before thee as incense; and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice.
Set*p a watch, O Lord,*s before my mouth; keep the door of my lips.
Incline*p not my heart to any evil thing, to practise wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their dainties.
Let*p the righteous smite me; it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me; it shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also shall be in their calamities.
When*p their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.
Our*p bones are scattered at the grave's mouth, as when one cutteth and cleaveth wood upon the earth.
But*p mine eyes are unto thee, O God*s the Lord: in thee is my trust; leave not my soul destitute.
Keep*p me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the gins of the workers of iniquity.
Let*p the wicked fall into their own nets, whilst that I withal escape.
